UNKNOWN — Mexico’s most-wanted drug lord, Joaquin Guzman a.k.a. El Chapo, has declared war on ISIS in an email to Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi, a prominent leader of the Islamic State, threatening that his cartel will wipe them off the planet. Actually, he hasn’t. The viral story was penned by Steve Charnock from Thug Life.

Charnock uploaded the story to cartelblog.com, writing that a Mexican blogger leaked the message after being sent the encrypted email from El Chapo to the ISIS leader. 

In this hoax story, Charnock wrote that El Chapo was angry because ISIS destroyed one of his drug shipments in the Middle East. 

The story was picked up by a number of media outlets around the world. The story contained fantastic details such as an angry email in which El Chapo wrote: “You are not soldiers. You are nothing but lowly p*ssies. Your god cannot save you from the true terror that my men will levy at you if you continue to impact my operation.” 

“My men will destroy you. The world is not yours to dictate. I pity the next son of a wh*re that tries to interfere with the business of the Sinaloa Cartel. I will have their heart and tongue torn from them.”

