SYRIA — In another diabolical scheme from the Islamic State terror group, unconfirmed photos of chickens strapped with loaded suicide belts have appeared on the Internet.

It seems that desperate jihadists fighting for the ISIS cause have begun to recruit unwilling hens to use as mobile explosive devices. The idea is that once the chickens have successfully infiltrated an enemy camp or at least come within striking distance the ISIS extremists remotely detonate the devices.

Chickens weren’t the first choice for the ISIS extremists. The suicide chicken photos began to appear a few days after a report of a suicide-goat-bomb targeting a Kurdish base. Perhaps the goat was too large to avoid enemy detection, which was why ISIS began using chickens?

It just seems like a desperate, bird-brained idea if you ask us.

